question.title: Will USA top the Olympic Medal Table at Paris 2024?
question.body:
This question will resolve positively if the United States Olympic Team are the (unique) highest ranked team at the 2024 Paris Olympics. It will resolve ambiguously if the Paris Olympics do not take place before 2027. It will resolve negatively if any team achieves a higher or equal ranking to the US team.

The medal table is calculated by taking all the medals won by each participating country and ordering by:

1. Number of Gold Medals
2. (Where 1 is tied) Number of Silver Medals
3. (Where 2 is tied) Number of Bronze Medals

para_P.title: Will the United States lead the Olympic Medal Count at the 2024 Paris Games?
para_P.body:
This inquiry will be considered affirmative if the U.S. Olympic Team is the sole highest-ranked team at the Paris 2024 Olympics. It will be deemed uncertain if the Paris Olympics do not occur prior to 2027. It will be regarded as negative if any other team matches or surpasses the ranking of the U.S. team.

The medal standings are determined by tallying the total medals earned by each participating nation and ranking them based on:

1. Total Gold Medals
2. (In case of a tie in Golds) Total Silver Medals
3. (In case of a tie in Silvers) Total Bronze Medals.

question.title: Will OpenAI's ChatGPT be generally available in the European Union on June 30, 2024?
question.body:
The question resolves as **YES** if [ChatGPT](chat.openai.com) is generally available in the EU on June 30, 2024, and **NO** otherwise.

"Generally available" here means that the default state for people in the EU is that they can access it without a VPN (possibly requiring paying for it.) If unavailable in certain EU countries (as was the case in Italy in early 2023), or unavailable to (for example) minors, this will still resolve positively, assuming at least >50% of the population can use it.

"ChatGPT" here refers to the general web interface (not the API) for interacting with GPT models. Still resolves positively if the name or website has changed, as long as OpenAI's service is substantially the same (entering queries to systems based on Large Language Models).

question.title: Stranded astronauts depart on Boeing Starliner by July 21?
question.body:
Clone of (and resolves identically to) https://polymarket.com/event/stranded-astronauts-depart-on-boeing-starliner-by-july-21?tid=1719805056151

The Boeing Starliner spacecraft, which arrived at the ISS on June 6, 2024, with NASA astronauts Suni Williams and Butch Wilmore, must depart within 45 days due to the Harmony module's limited fuel.

This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Boeing Starliner spacecraft departs the International Space Station (ISS) with NASA astronauts Suni Williams and Butch Wilmore by 11:59 PM ET on July 21, 2024. 

The Starliner will be considered to have departed if it has undocked from the ISS and begun its return journey to Earth.

The resolution source will be official announcements from NASA and/or Boeing, however a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

question.title: Will France place in the Top 5 at the 2024 Paris Olympics?
question.body:
This question will resolve positively if France place in the top 5 (ties resolve positively) at the Olympics being held in 2024. It will resolve ambiguously if the Olympics do not take place in 2024.

The medal table is calculated by taking the total number of medals won by each participating country and ordering by:

1. Number of Gold Medals
2. (Where 1 is tied) Number of Silver Medals
3. (Where 2 is tied) Number of Bronze Medal

para_P.title: Will France secure a spot in the Top 5 during the 2024 Paris Olympics?
para_P.body:
This inquiry will be considered affirmative if France secures a position in the top 5 (ties are counted as affirmative) at the Olympics scheduled for 2024. It will be deemed uncertain if the Olympics do not occur in 2024.

The medal standings are determined by summing the total medals earned by each competing nation and ranking them based on:

1. Total Gold Medals
2. (In case of ties for 1st) Total Silver Medals
3. (In case of ties for 2nd) Total Bronze Medals

question.title: Will diplomatic expulsions or recalls take place between the Philippines and China before August 1, 2024?
question.body:

- The Philippines expels at least one diplomat representing the People's Republic of China (PRC).

question.title: Facing Joe Biden instead of a generic Democrat, will Trump gain at least 3% among Manifold respondents?
question.body:
There are two Manifold polls posted, which both close on July 6.  One of the polls asks Manifold respondents to vote with Joe Biden on a hypothetical ballot, and another asks respondents to vote with a generic Democrat on the hypothetical ballot.

@/SteveSokolowski/1-of-2-given-these-choices-who-woul@/SteveSokolowski/2-of-2-given-these-choices-who-woul 

Public opinion polls consistently show Joe Biden losing to Donald Trump outside the margin of error, but every other Democrat hypothetically surveyed polls ahead or within the margin of error.  Are Manifold respondents representative of the general public?

This market will resolve YES if the percentage of votes for Donald Trump in poll 1 exceeds that in poll 2 by 3% or more when both polls close.

The formula for determining the percentage of votes for Trump is (Trump / (Trump + (the Democrat in the question) + Someone else)).  The answer is YES if this formula for poll 1 - the formula for poll 2 >= 0.03.  Otherwise, it is NO.

The polls and this question will never resolve N/A, and will remain open until the close time no matter what.

question.title: Will a group of at least 5 named Dem House Members or US Senators pressure Biden to drop out before July 20th?
question.body:
Politico reports:

Two safe-seat members have already publicly urged Biden out. Two of the most endangered Democrats told local news outlets they’ve already written off Biden’s chances to win in November.

Behind the scenes, things are even more frenzied. There are multiple drafts of letters circulating among House Democrats and at least one would call on Biden to end his campaign, according to five people familiar with the efforts.

This market resolves YES if a group of at least five named Democratic Party US House Members/US Senators work together to ask Joe Biden to consider ending his 2024 re-election campaign, or to urge him to do so, before Saturday July 20th (Pacific Time).

This could be by signing a letter like what is reported above, but it could also be in another form such as a group speaking with Biden in person and collectively asking him to drop out.

This market requires that all five individuals be part of the same group message. Five people separately telling reporters they think Biden should drop out is not sufficient for a YES resolution.

Reports of any number of unnamed democrats writing to Biden and asking him to step aside will not satisfy this market's criteria unless at least 5 qualifying names are later made public before this market's end date. In any ambiguous cases where such names are reported but not confirmed beyond a reasonable doubt, this market will err towards resolving NO. 

If these criteria are not met before July 20th, this market resolves NO.

para_P.title: Will at least five identified Democratic House Members or Senators compel Biden to withdraw before July 20th?
para_P.body:
According to Politico:

Two members from secure districts have already publicly called for Biden to step aside. Additionally, two of the most vulnerable Democrats have expressed to local media that they believe Biden's chances for victory in November are slim.

Behind the scenes, the situation is even more chaotic. There are several versions of letters being circulated among House Democrats, and at least one draft would request Biden to conclude his campaign, as per five individuals familiar with the discussions.

This market will resolve to YES if a coalition of at least five named Democratic Party US House Members or Senators collaborates to ask Joe Biden to contemplate ending his 2024 re-election campaign, or to strongly encourage him to do so, prior to Saturday, July 20th (Pacific Time).

This could occur through signing a letter similar to the one mentioned above, or through other means such as a group meeting with Biden in person to collectively request that he withdraw.

This market stipulates that all five individuals must be part of the same collective communication. If five individuals independently express to reporters their belief that Biden should step down, it will not count as a YES.

Reports of any number of unnamed Democrats reaching out to Biden to request he step aside will not meet the criteria for this market unless at least five qualifying names are disclosed publicly before the market closes. In cases where such names are reported but not confirmed with high certainty, the market will lean towards a NO resolution.

If these conditions are not fulfilled by July 20th, the market will resolve to NO.

question.title: Will Russian athletes be barred from competing at the 2024 Olympics?
question.body:
This question will resolve as **Yes** if Russian athletes are barred from competing at the 2024 Olympics under either (i) the Russian flag, (ii) The Russian Olympic Committee's flag, or (iii) any other independent or neutral flag. This will resolve based on the official list of countries and athletes present at the [2024 Olympics](https://olympics.com/en/olympic-games/paris-2024) or based on credible media reports, indicating that the 2024 Olympics are underway or have concluded without Russian participation. For the question to resolve as **Yes**, no more than 34 Russians can be competing at the 2024 Olympics. 34 was chosen as 10% of [Russian athletes that participated in the 2020 Olympics](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Olympic_Committee_athletes_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics) to allow for a few individual or sport specific exceptions.

If more than 34 Russian athletes compete at the 2024 Olympics, this question will resolve as **No**.

If the 2024 Olympics are cancelled or postponed to 2025 or afterwards, this question resolves as ambiguously.

question.title: Will Joe Biden have an in-person interview/conversation on camera for 45+ minutes, before the end of July 2024?
question.body:
The most recent qualifying interview was Biden's appearance on The Howard Stern Show in April, when Biden answered questions for ~70 minutes. 

If Biden appears in another such in-person interview for at least 45 minutes, this market resolves YES. If no qualifying interview is released before market close at the end of July, this market resolves NO. 

This market does not include press conferences, speeches, rallies, fundraisers, town halls, etc. It can include appearances on a podcast or late night show, or an interview edited into a show like 60 minutes. However, there must be at least 45 minutes of new footage of Biden being interviewed in-person for such appearances to count. A 50 minute video might only feature 20 minutes of video of Biden being interviewed, and so would not count.

For context, Biden's interview with Stephanopoulos in July, his appearance on Jimmy Fallon in February, and his past appearances on 60 minutes have each had less than 30 minutes of video footage of Biden being interviewed. 

You can find a list of Biden's interviews and their transcripts here.

question.title: Will OpenAI publicly commit to the "no retaliation for public risk disclosure" principle before July 1, 2024?
question.body:
This question resolves as **Yes** if, before July 1, 2024, both of the following are true:

- OpenAI publicly commits to the "no retaliation for public risk disclosure" principle via a statement from the company or a company spokesperson, such as Sam Altman. The statement may be formal (such as a press release) or informal (such as a tweet or quote in an interview). The statement from OpenAI must indicate a new level of commitment to the principle in question, relative to the time the righttowarn.ai statement was published; it cannot be a reiteration that, for example, "we already have a culture of open criticism".

This inquiry will receive a **Yes** answer if, prior to July 1, 2024, the following criteria are fulfilled:

- OpenAI issues a public commitment to the "no retaliation for public risk disclosure" policy via a declaration from the organization or a spokesperson, such as Sam Altman. This commitment can take the form of either a formal announcement (like a press release) or an informal one (such as a tweet or a remark made during an interview). The declaration must indicate a new dedication to the policy in comparison to the period when the righttowarn.ai statement was released; it cannot simply reiterate that, for example, "we already support open criticism".
- Metaculus verifies that the organization has adopted the policy to the satisfaction of at least one person from righttowarn.ai. Metaculus might reach out to particular signatories or supporters to assess their satisfaction with OpenAI's compliance. Statements must be at least as strong as "this was a positive initial step" for this question to be answered with **Yes**.

question.title: Will the same nation win more than one women's team sport at the 2024 Olympics?
question.body:
This question resolves as **No** if women's teams representing eight different National Olympic Committees (NOC) win gold in these eight team sports at the 2024 Paris Olympics: 

- association football 
- 3×3 basketball
- 5×5 basketball
- field hockey
- handball 
- rugby sevens
- volleyball
- water polo.

Otherwise, the same NOC must have won at least two of these events, so the question resolves as **Yes**.

The question can resolve as soon as it becomes clear one of these conditions will happen (e.g. neither team playing the final of the last event has won any of the others).

question.body:

question.title: Will the Venezuelan electoral commission publish full results of the July 28 presidential election before August 12, 2024?
question.body: This question resolves as Yes if [credible sources](https://www.metaculus.com/help/faq/#definitions) report that, before Monday, August 12, 2024 at 12:01 AM Venezuelan Standard Time (VET), any entity of the Venezuelan government has published results of the July 28, 2024 election purporting to represent 100% of the votes cast, disaggregated to the level of parish (*parroquia*, a subdivision of municipalities).

para_P.title: Will the full results of the presidential election held on July 28, 2024, be released by the Venezuelan electoral authority prior to August 12, 2024?
para_P.body: This inquiry will be answered affirmatively if [reliable sources](https://www.metaculus.com/help/faq/#definitions) indicate that, before 12:01 AM Venezuelan Standard Time (VET) on Monday, August 12, 2024, any Venezuelan governmental body has disclosed results of the July 28, 2024 election claiming to represent all votes cast, detailed down to the parish level (*parroquia*, a subdivision of municipalities).

para_P.body: This inquiry will be answered with a Yes if [reliable sources](https://www.metaculus.com/help/faq/#definitions) indicate that, before Monday, August 12, 2024 at 12:01 AM Venezuelan Standard Time (VET), any branch of the Venezuelan government has disclosed results of the July 28, 2024 election claiming to reflect 100% of the votes cast, broken down to the parish level (*parroquia*, a subdivision of municipalities).

question.title: Did someone intentionally shoot at Trump on July 13th?
question.body:
NYT: "It sounded what could be gun shots interrupted Trump’s rally in Pennsylvania. Trump was hurried off the stage and appeared to be bleeding by his ear."

Resolves YES if someone intentionally shot a bullet or other bullet-like projectile* at Trump on July 13th. Resolves NO if accidental discharge or ricochet caused something to shoot towards Trump.

*I am using bullet-like projectile to mean something that is for all intents and purposes is a bullet but may not technically be a bullet. For example, I would not count a BB gun pellet since it is not plausibly lethal like a bullet would be.

para_P.title: Was there a deliberate shooting aimed at Trump on July 13th?
para_P.body:
According to NYT: "The sound of what seemed like gunfire disrupted Trump’s rally in Pennsylvania. Trump was quickly taken off the stage and appeared to have a wound near his ear."

This resolves to YES if an individual deliberately fired a bullet or similar projectile at Trump on July 13th. It resolves to NO if the incident was caused by an accidental discharge or ricochet that directed something towards Trump.

*The term bullet-like projectile refers to any object that functions similarly to a bullet in its intended purpose, although it may not be classified as a traditional bullet. For instance, a BB gun pellet would not be included since it is not considered lethal like a bullet.

para_P.title: Was there a deliberate shooting at Trump on July 13th?

According to the NYT: "It sounded like what could be gunfire interrupted Trump’s rally in Pennsylvania. Trump was quickly taken off the stage and seemed to have a wound near his ear."

This resolves to YES if an individual aimed and fired a bullet or similar projectile at Trump on July 13th. It resolves to NO if the incident was due to an accidental discharge or a ricochet that resulted in something being directed towards Trump.

*The term bullet-like projectile refers to any object that functions similarly to a bullet, even if it is not technically classified as one. For example, a BB gun pellet would not be included, as it is not likely to be lethal like a bullet.

question.title: Will at least 20 House/Senate Democrats sign a public letter opposing the plan to virtually nominate Biden early?
question.body:
Context from Politico:

Dozens of House Democrats are organizing a plan to speak out against their own party’s effort to seal President Joe Biden’s nomination sooner than originally planned, which they argue stifles the intense ongoing debate about his candidacy, according to a lawmaker involved in the effort.

A drafted letter, circulated by Rep. Jared Huffman (D-Calif.) and obtained by POLITICO, offers the first public signal from Democrats since the weekend’s attempted assassination on former President Donald Trump that scores of their own members remain deeply unsettled about the future of Biden’s candidacy.

“It’s a really bad move by the DNC. Somebody thinks it’s a clever way to lock down debate and I guess by dint of sheer force, achieve unity, but it doesn’t work that way,” Huffman said in an interview. He declined to confirm the existence of a letter.

This market resolves YES if a public letter opposing the early nomination plan is signed by at least 20 House Members or Senators who caucus with the Democratic Party before market close at the end of Sunday, July 21st. 

Multiple such letters with a combined total of 20 lawmaker's signatures would also be sufficient to resolve this market to YES. 

If these criteria are not met by market close, this market resolves NO.

question.title: Will Trump's lead over Biden be greater than 2 and less than or equal to 4 on July 15, 2024, according to 538's national polling average?
question.body:
This question will resolve as Donald Trump's lead over Joe Biden in 538's [national polling average for the 2024 presidential election](https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/polls/president-general/2024/national/) as reported on the chart for the date of July 15, 2024, when accessed by Metaculus on July 17, 2024.

For the purposes of this question, a positive value means a Trump lead, while a negative value means Biden is leading. For example, as of July 5, 2024, the value reported for July 5 is Trump 2.4 points ahead of Biden, which would be a positive value of 2.4 for this purposes of this question.

para_P.title: On July 15, 2024, will Donald Trump's advantage over Joe Biden exceed 2 but not surpass 4 according to 538's average of national polls?
para_P.body:
This inquiry will conclude based on the difference in favor of Donald Trump over Joe Biden as indicated by 538's [national polling average for the 2024 presidential election](https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/polls/president-general/2024/national/) on the chart dated July 15, 2024, when viewed by Metaculus on July 17, 2024.

In this context, a positive figure signifies a lead for Trump, whereas a negative figure indicates Biden is in the lead. For instance, on July 5, 2024, the reported figure shows Trump ahead of Biden by 2.4 points, which would be a positive figure of 2.4 for the purposes of this question.

para_P.title: On July 15, 2024, will the margin by which Trump is ahead of Biden range between 2 and 4 according to 538's national polling average?

question.title: Will "Twisters" (2024) have a Rotten Tomatoes critics score of at least 75%? ("Certified Fresh")
question.body:
"Twisters" (2024) Rotten Tomatoes page

This resolves YES if the Tomatometer score is 75% or higher, one week after release (July 26th). 

Details 

I will use whatever precision is listed by Rotten Tomatoes (typically an integer percentage, no decimal).

For example, the original "Twister" (1996) currently has a Tomatometer of 63%. This is the equivalent score I will use.

"Certified Fresh" is just used for illustrative purposes (AFAIK, it requires >=75% Tomatometer, but there might be other restrictions—the market resolves solely based on the displayed score).

"Twisters" (2024) is a standalone sequel to the 1996 original, directed by Lee Isaac Chung ("Minari"), starring Glen Powell ("Top Gun: Maverick") and Daisy Edgar Jones ("Normal People").

question.title: Will Liz Cheney be the Republican nominee for the 2024 US Presidential Election?
question.body:
This question will resolve as **Yes** if Liz Cheney is selected by the Republican National Convention as the nominee for the 2024 US Presidential Election. All other candidates will resolve as **No**. This question is not restricted to the candidates currently listed; other options may be added in the future.

For this question, it is not relevant who receives the Republican nomination on the day of the 2024 US election; it is solely determined by who is selected by the delegates of the [Republican National Convention](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republican_National_Convention).

para_P.title: Will Liz Cheney be the Republican candidate for the 2024 US Presidential Election?
para_P.body:
This inquiry will conclude as **Yes** if Liz Cheney is chosen by the Republican National Convention as the candidate for the 2024 US Presidential Election. question.title: Will Biden be declared incapacitated under the 25th Amendment Section 4 before August?
question.body:
Resolves YES if the Vice President and a majority of the Cabinet (or other relevant body) invokes Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to formally declare that "the President is unable to discharge the powers and duties of his office" and cause the Vice President to serve as Acting President, before August 2024 (Eastern time).

The duration of the incapacity does not matter for this question.

Biden exiting the office of the Presidency by death, resignation, etc does not count. Biden invoking section 3 of the 25th amendment does not count.

Context: GOP lawmaker asks Merrick Garland to invoke 25th Amendment to remove Biden from office

para_P.title: Will the 25th Amendment Section 4 be used to declare Biden incapacitated prior to August?
para_P.body:
This will be considered a YES if the Vice President along with a majority of the Cabinet (or another appropriate body) activates Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to officially state that "the President is unable to fulfill the powers and responsibilities of his office" and appoint the Vice President as Acting President, before August 2024 (Eastern time).

The length of the incapacity is not relevant for this inquiry.

Biden leaving the Presidency due to death, resignation, etc., is not included. Biden's use of Section 3 of the 25th Amendment does not apply.

para_P.title: Will Biden be deemed unable to fulfill his presidential responsibilities under Section 4 of the 25th Amendment prior to August?
para_P.body:
This question will be answered with a YES if the Vice President along with a majority of the Cabinet (or another appropriate body) activates Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to officially state that "the President is unable to discharge the powers and duties of his office" and appoints the Vice President as Acting President, before August 2024 (Eastern time).

The length of the incapacity is irrelevant for this inquiry.

Biden leaving the presidency due to death, resignation, or similar circumstances does not apply. Biden's own invocation of Section 3 of the 25th Amendment is also excluded.

Context: A GOP lawmaker has requested Merrick Garland to invoke the 25th Amendment for Biden's removal from office.

para_P.title: Is there a possibility that Biden will be considered unable to carry out his presidential duties under Section 4 of the 25th Amendment before August?
para_P.body:
This inquiry will receive a YES response if the Vice President, along with a majority of the Cabinet (or another relevant authority), activates Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to formally declare that "the President is unable to perform the powers and responsibilities of his office" and appoints the Vice President as Acting President, prior to August 2024 (Eastern time).

The duration of the incapacity does not matter for this question.

Biden's exit from the presidency due to death, resignation, or similar events is not applicable. Additionally, Biden's own use of Section 3 of the 25th Amendment is excluded.

Context: A Republican lawmaker has urged Merrick Garland to invoke the 25th Amendment for Biden's removal from office.

para_P.title: Will Biden be deemed incapacitated according to Section 4 of the 25th Amendment prior to August?
para_P.body:
Determines YES if the Vice President along with a majority of the Cabinet (or other pertinent authority) activates Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to officially state that "the President is unable to perform the powers and responsibilities of his office" and enable the Vice President to act as President, before August 2024 (Eastern time).

The length of the incapacity is not relevant to this inquiry.

Biden leaving the Presidential position due to death, resignation, etc., is not included. Biden activating section 3 of the 25th amendment is also not included.

Context: A GOP legislator requests Merrick Garland to invoke the 25th Amendment to remove Biden from his position.

para_P.title: Will the 25th Amendment's Section 4 declare Biden incapacitated before August?
para_P.body:
Determines YES if the Vice President, along with a majority of the Cabinet (or other relevant authority), enacts Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to formally declare that "the President is unable to perform the powers and responsibilities of his office" and allows the Vice President to assume the role of President, prior to August 2024 (Eastern time).

The duration of the incapacity is not pertinent to this question.

The duration of the incapacity is not pertinent to this question.

Biden's departure from the Presidential role due to death, resignation, etc., is not considered. Biden's invocation of section 3 of the 25th amendment is also excluded.

question.title: Will Biden be deemed unable to fulfill his presidential duties under the 25th Amendment Section 4 before August?

The length of the incapacity is irrelevant to this question.

question.title: Will Blake Lively's "It Ends With Us" outgross her husband Ryan Reynold's "Deadpool & Wolverine" this weekend?
question.body:
Resolution 

This market resolves YES "It Ends with Us" has a higher (domestic) gross than "Deadpool & Wolverine" for the weekend of August 9-11. 

Source: The "weekend" tab in BoxOfficeMojo, for August 9-11.

I will use the number listed by BoxOfficeMojo, however it is defined (e.g. typically 3-day FSS wekeend + previews).

Example: last weekend, the "Deadpool & Wolverine" grossed $96.8M, far ahead of the "Trap", which opened to $15.4M.

Context 

"Deadpool & Wolverine" has been crushing the box office, and is expected to repeat with its 3rd weekend at #1. 

The potential long shot that could dethrone it is "It Ends With Us", the adaptation of Colleen Hoover's mega-bestseller, starring (funnily enough) Ryan Reynold's wife, Blake Lively.

question.title: [Metaculus] Will diplomatic expulsions or recalls take place between the Philippines and China before August 1, 2024?
question.body:
Will diplomatic expulsions or recalls take place between the Philippines and China before August 1, 2024?

Resolves the same as the original on Metaculus.

(https://www.metaculus.com/questions/question_embed/24034/?theme=dark)Resolution criteria

This question resolves as Yes if before August 1, 2024, one of these four events happens, according to official statements or credible reports:

The Philippines expels at least one diplomat representing the People's Republic of China (PRC).

The Philippines recalls at least one of its diplomats stationed in the PRC.

The PRC expels at least one diplomat representing the Philippines.

The PRC recalls at least one of its diplomats stationed in the Philippines.

If there are no such reports before that date, then this resolves as No.

Fine print and additional background information can be found on Metaculus.

question.title: Will at least 30% of Manifold respondents agree that weak AGI had been achieved before July 23, 2024?
question.body:
[image]Every month, a Manifold poll is being posted to gain the consensus view of progress towards AGI. Unlike many of the markets and questions on Manifold, these polls will simply ask "has weak AGI been achieved," rather than providing a definition of the term. The goal is that given that the term is so broad, the only way to characterize AI progress is also to allow respondents to vote based upon their own understanding.

Progress has been steady.  The previous polls are referenced here:

@/SteveSokolowski/did-openai-achieve-weak-agi-with-gp  (Answer: 15)

@/SteveSokolowski/june-2024-has-weak-agi-been-achieve  (Answer: 27)

The previous markets on this topic, which significantly understimated Manifold's belief in AI progress, were:

@/SteveSokolowski/what-percentage-of-manifold-poll-re 

@/SteveSokolowski/will-at-least-20-of-manifold-respon 

The polls will not reference any specific model, and will not define "AGI" except to state that the poll does not require that the software system be able to manipulate the physical world. The polls open on the 23rd of each month and close on the 30th.

This market will resolve to YES if the July 2024 poll results in a ratio of YES/(NO + YES) greater than or equal to 0.3. The "no opinion" respondents will be ignored. Otherwise, this question will resolve to NO.

See also:

@/SteveSokolowski/will-one-of-the-monthly-has-weak-ag

question.title: Will a journalist or an opposition politician be charged in connection with the assassination attempt on Slovak PM Robert Fico, before June 15, 2024?
question.body:

Alternatively, the resolution will also be **YES** if relevant Slovak institutions (e.g., the public prosecutor's office, courts, police, and similar authorities) issue a statement to that effect.

Otherwise, the question will be resolved as **NO**.

question.title: Iran military response before August 13th midnight Eastern Time?
question.body:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Iran initiates a military action on Israeli soil, airspace, or maritime territory between July 30 and August 12, 2024, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

For the purposes of this market, a "military action" will be considered to be any use of force executed by Iran on Israeli soil, airspace, or maritime territory (e.g. if a weapons depot on Israeli soil is hit by an Iranian missile, this market will resolve to "Yes") that is officially acknowledged by the Iranian government or a consensus of credible reporting. This includes, but is not limited to, airstrikes, naval attacks, or ground invasions. Cyber attacks, sanctions, or diplomatic actions will not count towards the resolution of this market.

Only responses by Iranian forces explicitly claimed by the Islamic Republic of Iran, or confirmed to have originated from Iranian territory will count toward the resolution of this market. Attacks on Israel by proxy forces (i.e. Hezbollah, Houthis, etc.) will not count toward the resolution of this market.

For this market, a "military operation" refers to any aggressive act conducted by Iran against Israeli territory, airspace, or waters (for instance, if an Iranian missile strikes a weapons facility in Israel, the market will settle on "Yes") that is officially recognized by the Iranian government or corroborated by reliable reports. This encompasses, but is not limited to, airstrikes, naval assaults, or ground invasions. Cyber warfare, economic sanctions, or diplomatic measures will not be considered for this market's resolution.

question.title: Will Rishi Sunak fail to be elected in the 2024 UK General Election?
question.body:
This question resolves as **Yes** if for any reason Rishi Sunak fails to be elected as a Member of Parliament in the July 4 2024 UK general election.

If Sunak is elected as a Member of Parliament for any constituency in the July 4 2024 UK general election, this question will resolve as **No**.

Resolution should cite [credible](https://www.metaculus.com/help/faq/#definitions) media reports, or an official announcement from the returning officer of the constituency in which Sunak is a candidate (if he is a candidate in any constituency).

para_P.body:
This inquiry will conclude as **Yes** if Rishi Sunak does not secure a position as a Member of Parliament in the UK general election taking place on July 4, 2024.

Conversely, if Sunak does achieve election as a Member of Parliament for any constituency during the July 4, 2024 UK general election, the outcome will be recorded as **No**.

The resolution must reference [credible](https://www.metaculus.com/help/faq/#definitions) news sources, or an official declaration from the returning officer of the constituency where Sunak is contesting (if he is indeed a candidate in any constituency).

This inquiry will be considered resolved as **Yes** if Rishi Sunak does not secure election as a Member of Parliament in the UK general election scheduled for July 4, 2024.

Conversely, if Sunak wins a seat as a Member of Parliament for any constituency during the July 4, 2024 UK general election, this question will be seen as resolved as **No**.

The resolution must reference [reliable](https://www.metaculus.com/help/faq/#definitions) news sources, or an official statement from the returning officer of the constituency where Sunak is standing (if he is indeed a candidate in any constituency).

question.title: Will 538 Project Biden as the favorite on Friday?
question.body:
This market will resolve to “Yes” if Joe Biden has a higher probability of winning the US presidential election than Donald Trump according to the FiveThirtyEight election forecast for the day of July 19, 2024. This market will resolve to “No” if Donald Trump has a higher probability of winning the US presidential election than Joe Biden according to the FiveThirtyEight election forecast for the day of July 19, 2024. If Biden and Trump have equal odds, this market will resolve 50-50.

The resolution source will be FiveThirtyEight's 2024 presidential election forecast, https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/2024-election-forecast/, specifically the numbers indicated by the blue and red trend lines for this market's resolution date. Changes in the methodology by which FiveThirtyEight calculates its figures will have no bearing on the resolution of this market.

This market will resolve according to the datapoints for July 19 as soon as datapoints for July 20 become available. This market may not resolve until the July 20 datapoints are available. If no datapoints for July 19 are available by July 22, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve according to the nearest previous figures to July 19.

Please note the resolution refers to the odds of each candidate winning as a number out of 100 reported to the 1 digit mark (eg. "Trump 57 times out of 100"). The listed number of simulations out of 1,000 won by each candidate will NOT be considered.

para_P.title: Will FiveThirtyEight consider Biden the frontrunner on Friday?
para_P.body:
This market will conclude with a “Yes” if Joe Biden is assessed to have a greater chance of winning the US presidential election compared to Donald Trump, based on the FiveThirtyEight election forecast for July 19, 2024. Conversely, it will conclude with a “No” if Donald Trump is evaluated to have a superior probability of winning the US presidential election over Joe Biden, according to the FiveThirtyEight election forecast for that same date. In the event that both candidates have equal probabilities, the market will resolve 50-50.

The resolution will rely on FiveThirtyEight's 2024 presidential election forecast, accessible at https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/2024-election-forecast/, specifically using the data indicated by the blue and red trend lines for the date of resolution. Any changes in the methodology used by FiveThirtyEight to derive its figures will not affect the outcome of this market.

The market will resolve based on the data for July 19 once the data for July 20 becomes available. It may not reach a conclusion until the July 20 data is accessible. If no data for July 19 is available by July 22, 11:59 PM ET, the market will resolve based on the closest prior figures to July 19.

Please be aware that the resolution pertains to the winning odds of each candidate expressed as a number out of 100, rounded to one decimal place (for example, "Trump 57 out of 100"). The number of simulations won by each candidate out of 1,000 will not be taken into account.

question.title: Will TCB Scans upload chapter 1122 of One Piece on August 1st?
question.body:
https://manifold.markets/news/shortfuse-one-piece

I am basing this off of GMT-7 time zone for July 18th If they release chapter 1122 between 00:00:00 and 23:59:59, this question will resolve as “YES.” Anything else will resolve as “NO.”

TCB Scans usually posts the chapter on the Thursday before official release. 1121. 1120, 1119, 1118, 1117, 1116 and 1115 were Thursdays. 1114 was a Thursday, May 9th. 1113 was a Friday, April 25th. 1112 was a Friday, April 19. 1111 will be uploaded March 22, a Friday. 1110 was uploaded March 15th, a Friday. 1109 was uploaded March 1, a Friday. 1108 was February 22, 1107 was February 15, both Thursdays. 

TCB has started posting on Fridays after the twitter account ban. Unknown if this shall continue, thought I’d put the info here for investors.

I do not answer my own questions.

question.title: Will Biden remain President through end of July 2024?
question.body:
Resolves YES if Biden remains US President through the end of July 2024 (ET); resolves NO if he resigns, dies, or otherwise ceases to be President before then.

Temporary transfer of power under the 25th amendement (i.e. making his VP the Acting President) does not cause a YES resolution. (Acting President is different from President under the Constitution)

para_P.title: Is Biden expected to hold the presidency until the conclusion of July 2024?
para_P.body:
This resolves to YES if Biden continues to be the President of the United States until the end of July 2024 (ET); it resolves to NO if he steps down, passes away, or otherwise stops being President before that date.

A temporary delegation of authority under the 25th amendment (such as appointing his Vice President as Acting President) does not result in a YES resolution. (An Acting President is not the same as the President according to the Constitution)

para_P.title: Will Biden still be in office as President by the conclusion of July 2024?
para_P.body:
This will be considered a YES if Biden is still serving as the President of the United States at the end of July 2024 (ET); it will be a NO if he resigns, passes away, or otherwise stops being President prior to that date.

A temporary transfer of authority under the 25th amendment (for instance, appointing his Vice President as Acting President) does not lead to a YES outcome. (An Acting President is distinct from a President according to the Constitution)

para_P.title: Will Biden remain in his role as President by the end of July 2024?
para_P.body:
This will be marked as a YES if Biden continues to hold the position of President of the United States at the conclusion of July 2024 (ET); it will be a NO if he resigns, dies, or otherwise ceases to be President before that date.

A temporary delegation of power under the 25th amendment (such as designating his Vice President as Acting President) does not result in a YES outcome. (An Acting President is not the same as a President according to the Constitution)

para_P.title: Will Biden continue to serve as President until the conclusion of July 2024?
para_P.body:
Resolves YES if Biden is still the US President at the close of July 2024 (ET); resolves NO if he steps down, passes away, or otherwise stops being President prior to that date.

A temporary delegation of authority under the 25th amendment (such as appointing his Vice President as the Acting President) does not result in a YES resolution. (The role of Acting President differs from that of President according to the Constitution)

para_P.title: Will Biden remain in office as President until the end of July 2024?
para_P.body:
This will be answered with YES if Biden is still serving as the President of the United States at the end of July 2024 (Eastern Time); it will be answered with NO if he resigns, dies, or otherwise ceases to be President before that date.

A temporary transfer of power under the 25th amendment (like appointing his Vice President as Acting President) does not count as a YES answer. (The position of Acting President is distinct from that of President according to the Constitution)

para_P.title: Will Biden remain in office as President until the end of July 2024?
para_P.body:

question.title: Will Donald Trump be removed or blocked from the primary election ballot of any U.S. state for a federal office under Section 3 of the 14th Amendment?
question.body:
This question will resolve as "Yes" if, *on* July 15, 2024:

Donald Trump has been officially removed or blocked from the primary election ballot of any U.S. state for a federal office (President, Senate, House of Representatives) under the grounds of Section 3 of the 14th Amendment.

The removal or block is confirmed through official state government announcements, court decisions, legal documentation, or credible media reports. Speculative reports, opinion pieces, or unofficial announcements will not suffice for resolution.

The question will resolve as "No" if these conditions are not met as of July 15, 2024.

Note: The question does not account for legal battles, appeals, or subsequent reversals that might occur *after* the mentioned date. It strictly pertains to whether Donald Trump has been removed from any state's primary election ballot for a federal office under the specified grounds as of July 15, 2024. If Trump is removed or blocked from a ballot and then reinstated, such that as of July 15th he is not removed or blocked from any ballot, the question resolves negatively.

question.title: Will Tucker Carlson be the Republican nominee for the 2024 US Presidential Election?
question.body:
This question will resolve as **Yes** if Tucker Carlson is selected by the Republican National Convention as the nominee for the 2024 US Presidential Election. Any other candidate being selected will resolve as **No**. This question is not restricted to the candidates currently listed; other options may be added in the future.

For this question, it is not relevant who receives the Republican nomination on the day of the 2024 US election; it is solely determined by who is selected by the delegates of the [Republican National Convention](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republican_National_Convention).

question.title: Will the same nation win more than one women's team sport at the 2024 Olympics?
question.body:
This question resolves as No if women's teams representing eight different National Olympic Committees (NOC) win gold in the eight team sports - association football, 3×3 basketball, 5×5 basketball, field hockey, handball, rugby sevens, voleyball and water polo.

Otherwise, the same NOC must have won at least two of these events, so the question resolves as **Yes**.

para_P.title: Is it possible for a single country to secure victories in multiple women's team sports during the 2024 Olympic Games?
para_P.body:

question.title: Will Scotland hold an official, sanctioned referendum on independence before May 3, 2024?
question.body:
This question will resolve as **Yes** if there is a referendum held in Scotland regarding Scotland's independence from the United Kingdom, and this referendum is held before May 3, 2024.  This referendum may be an "advisory" referendum; that is, it is not necessary for the referendum to have any legally binding effect.

It shall not be deemed resolved by a “wildcat” or “Catalan” style of referendum where the UK government has declined permission for the vote, nor by a vote organised by civil society institutions. A referendum must be deemed to have the consent of the London government

question.title: Will a terrorist act occur in metropolitan France during the 2024 Summer Olympics?
question.body:
The question will resolve as Yes if a terrorist attack in [Metropolitan France](https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metropolitan_France) injures and/or kills at least one person, other than the terrorist(s), between, and inclusive of, the day of the Opening Ceremony (26 July 2024) and the day of the Closing Ceremony (11 August 2024). The question will resolve as No if the above does not happen.

An event will be considered a 'terrorist attack' if it is described as such by any agency of the State of France, or by the French President, Prime Minister, or a member of the Council of Ministers.

para_P.title: Is there a possibility of a terrorist incident happening in metropolitan France during the 2024 Summer Olympics?
para_P.body:
This inquiry will be answered in the affirmative if a terrorist incident in [Metropolitan France](https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metropolitan_France) results in injuries and/or fatalities to at least one individual, excluding the terrorist(s), from the day of the Opening Ceremony (26 July 2024) to the day of the Closing Ceremony (11 August 2024). Conversely, the response will be negative if the above conditions are not met.

An occurrence will be classified as a 'terrorist incident' if it is labeled as such by any governmental body of France, or by the French President, Prime Minister, or a member of the Council of Ministers.

This inquiry will receive a Yes if a terrorist act takes place in [Metropolitan France](https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metropolitan_France) resulting in the injury or death of at least one individual, excluding the terrorists, from the start of the Opening Ceremony (26 July 2024) until the end of the Closing Ceremony (11 August 2024), inclusive. A No will be given if the specified circumstances do not happen.

An occurrence will be classified as a 'terrorist act' if it is recognized as such by any French governmental body, or by the President, Prime Minister, or a member of the Council of Ministers of France.

An incident will be classified as a 'terrorist attack' if it is recognized as such by any governmental body in France, or by the French President, Prime Minister, or a member of the Council of Ministers.

A No will be given if this situation does not take place.

An event will be regarded as a 'terrorist incident' if it is acknowledged as such by any official authority in France, or by the President, Prime Minister, or a member of the Council of Ministers.

question.title: Will at least 50 Kenyan military or police personnel arrive in Haiti before June 1, 2024?
question.body: This question will resolve as **Yes** if, after May 22, 2024, and before June 1, 2024, credible sources report that at least 50 Kenyan military or police personnel have arrived in Haiti.

para_P.title: Are there going to be a minimum of 50 members of the Kenyan military or police deployed to Haiti prior to June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This inquiry will be considered **Yes** if, between May 22, 2024, and June 1, 2024, reliable sources indicate that no fewer than 50 Kenyan military or police personnel have been sent to Haiti.

para_P.title: Are 50 or more members of the Kenyan military or police expected to reach Haiti prior to June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This inquiry will be considered **Yes** if, between May 22, 2024, and June 1, 2024, reliable sources confirm that a minimum of 50 Kenyan military or police personnel have arrived in Haiti.

para_P.title: Is it anticipated that at least 50 individuals from the Kenyan armed forces or law enforcement will arrive in Haiti before June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This question will be deemed **Yes** if credible sources verify that no fewer than 50 members of the Kenyan military or police have reached Haiti between May 22, 2024, and June 1, 2024.

para_P.title: Will a minimum of 50 members of the Kenyan military or police reach Haiti prior to June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This inquiry will be answered as **Yes** if, between May 22, 2024, and June 1, 2024, reliable sources indicate that at least 50 members of the Kenyan military or police have arrived in Haiti.

para_P.title: Is it expected that at least 50 personnel from the Kenyan armed forces or law enforcement will arrive in Haiti before June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This question will be marked as **Yes** if credible sources report that a minimum of 50 members of the Kenyan armed forces or police have reached Haiti during the period from May 22, 2024, to June 1, 2024.

para_P.title: Is it expected that at least 50 personnel from the Kenyan military or police will arrive in Haiti before June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This question will be considered answered with **Yes** if credible sources confirm that a minimum of 50 members of the Kenyan military or police have landed in Haiti between May 22, 2024, and June 1, 2024.

para_P.title: Will a minimum of 50 members of the Kenyan armed forces or law enforcement be present in Haiti prior to June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This inquiry will be deemed answered with **Yes** if reliable sources verify that at least 50 personnel from the Kenyan military or police have arrived in Haiti during the period from May 22, 2024, to June 1, 2024.

question.title: Will a minimum of 50 Kenyan military or law enforcement officers reach Haiti before June 1, 2024?
question.body: This inquiry will conclude as **Yes** if, between May 22, 2024, and June 1, 2024, trustworthy sources confirm that no fewer than 50 Kenyan military or police officers have reached Haiti.

para_P.title: Will at least 50 members of the Kenyan military or police arrive in Haiti prior to June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This question will be answered with **Yes** if, during the period from May 22, 2024, to June 1, 2024, reliable sources verify that a minimum of 50 Kenyan military or law enforcement personnel have arrived in Haiti.

para_P.title: Will at least 50 members of the Kenyan military or police arrive in Haiti prior to June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This question will be answered with **Yes** if credible sources verify that at least 50 Kenyan military personnel or law enforcement officers have arrived in Haiti between May 22, 2024, and June 1, 2024.

para_P.title: Are there going to be a minimum of 50 individuals from the Kenyan armed forces or police present in Haiti before June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This inquiry will receive a response of **Yes** if reliable sources confirm that no fewer than 50 members of the Kenyan military or police have reached Haiti during the period from May 22, 2024, to June 1, 2024.

para_P.title: Will at least 50 officers from the Kenyan military or police arrive in Haiti prior to June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This question will be answered with **Yes** if reliable sources verify that at least 50 military or law enforcement personnel from Kenya have arrived in Haiti between May 22, 2024, and June 1, 2024.

para_P.title: Are there expected to be a minimum of 50 members of the Kenyan armed forces or police present in Haiti before June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This inquiry will receive a response of **Yes** if trustworthy sources confirm that no fewer than 50 military or law enforcement officers from Kenya have reached Haiti during the period from May 22, 2024, to June 1, 2024.

para_P.title: Are there expected to be a minimum of 50 members of the Kenyan military or police who will reach Haiti before June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: This question will receive a response of **Yes** if credible sources confirm that no fewer than 50 military or law enforcement officers from Kenya have landed in Haiti during the period from May 22, 2024, to June 1, 2024.

para_P.title: Is it anticipated that at least 50 personnel from the Kenyan armed forces or police will arrive in Haiti prior to June 1, 2024?
para_P.body: A response of **Yes** will be given if reliable sources verify that at least 50 members of the military or police from Kenya have arrived in Haiti between May 22, 2024, and June 1, 2024.
